%% Diagram: Circuit Breaker States and Transitions
%% Type: state
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Closed

    state "Closed\nrequests pass through\nfailure rate counted" as Closed
    state "Open\nfast-fail every request\ntimer running" as Open
    state "Half-Open\nallow N probe requests\nmeasure outcome" as HalfOpen

    Closed --> Open: failure rate >= threshold\n(e.g. 50 percent over window)
    Open --> HalfOpen: cool-down elapsed\n(e.g. 30 s)
    HalfOpen --> Closed: probes succeed\nreset failure counters
    HalfOpen --> Open: any probe fails\nrestart cool-down timer

    note right of Open
        Backoff retries are skipped
        while open; the breaker IS
        the backoff at this point.
    end note

    note right of HalfOpen
        Tune probe count low: too
        many probes re-overload a
        recovering backend.
    end note
